          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets of isotopically enriched Sm-147 98% and Sm-149",
                " 97.4% with thicknesses of 40-mug/cm**2 and",
                " 125-mug/cm**2, respectively, evaporated onto thin",
                "carbon backings were used.",
                "The Yb-evaporation residues were trapped in an Al-foil",
                "of 800-mug/cm**2, which was placed 2-mm behind the",
                "samarium target. The thickness of the catcher foil was",
                "sufficient to stop the evaporation residues letting",
                "through the products of the reaction of O-16 with the",
                "oxygen impurity in the target, with the carbon of the",
                "target backing and with the aluminium of the some",
                "catcher foil. During selected runs a second catcher",
                "foil was located behind the first one in order to",
                "verify that none of the evaporation residues was lost."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Statistical model calculations of the x-n",
                "distributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "3ARGCNE"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 20-UD tandem accelerator at the",
                " tandar-laboratory in Buenos Aires."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two surface barrier silicon counters were",
                "placed at +-30-degree to the beam and at a distance",
                "of 31-cm from the target for monitoring the elastic and",
                "inelastic scattering of O-16 with the samarium",
                "isotopes.",
                "Following irradiations of about 100-120 min, the",
                "catcher foils were removed from the scattering chamber",
                "and placed in front of a 5-cm**3 Ge-planar X-ray",
                "detector. The X-ray detector had an energy resolution",
                "of 480-eV(FWHM) at 50-KeV. The absolute photopeak",
                "efficiency of the detector was determined using a set",
                "of calibrated sources that were carefully mounted in",
                "the same geometry as the catcher  foils. The efficiency",
                "was 3.7+-1.2% at an energy of 40-60-KeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Corrections were made for summing effects",
                "due to the simultaneous detection of more than one",
                "photon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The error from the absolute normalization based",
                "on rutherford scattering is 9%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The error from the absolute efficiency of the",
                "X-ray detector is 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The error in the coefficients of expression",
                "is 10%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The error on the cross section arising from the",
                "statistical uncertainty in the peak areas and the",
                "fitting of the decay curves. There error were typically",
                " 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".By summing in quadrature the different sources",
                "of error (see above), excluding beam energy an overall",
                "error of approx. 12% in the fusion cross sections was",
                "calculated. The errors are higher 15-20% at lowest",
                "bombarding energies, where the counting statistics were",
                "lower. See table 2."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The absolute energy of the O-16 beam has an",
                "uncertainty of +-0.5%, which has been determined by",
                "calibrating the 90-degree analyzing magnet of the",
                "tandem accelerator ."
              ]
            }
